-- Embraer, BNDES to set up $59 mln fund for Brazil aerospace industry
-- 
-- Wed May 07, 2014 08:13AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, May 7 (Reuters) - Embraer SA <EMBR3.SA><ERJ.N>, the world's largest regional aircraft maker, will set up a 131 million real ($59 million) investment fund for projects in the Brazilian aerospace industry alongside a number of state entities, according to a securities filing on Wednesday.

Embraer will start the fund with state development bank BNDES [BNDES.UL], the São Paulo State Development Agency and Finep, a federal government-funded research and development institution, according to the filing.